SuGar Yoshinaga (Guitars, Vocals) and Yumiko Ohno (Bass, Keys, Vocals) formed an all female quartet in 1987 called Havana Exotica. They released 2 albums and began attracting attention, but broke up soon after. SuGar and Yumiko went on to join forces with turntablist, Mooog Yamamoto and formed Buffalo Daughter in 1993.
